declarations.comments: Run the emo8 game in development mode.
declarations.title: emo8Dev

declarations.comments: Emo8 color type which supports 140 HTML named colors.
declarations.title: Color

declarations.comments: Emo8 emoji type which supports 1329 (Unicode v13.0) single code point emojis.
declarations.title: Emoji

declarations.comments: Emo8 note type which supports the scales from A4 (440Hz) to A5 (880Hz).
declarations.title: Note

declarations.comments: Emo8 tone type which supports OscillatorNode's basic wave types (WebAudioAPI).
declarations.title: Tone

declarations.comments: Local storage key type to save the game state for emo8 development mode.
declarations.title: LocalKey

children.comments: It takes input and current state and should return next state.
children.title: update

children.comments: It takes next state and runs some draw operations.
children.title: draw

children.comments: It takes next state and runs some sound operations.
children.title: sound

declarations.comments:
Emo8 basic game class.

Update, draw, sound functions are called in order each frames.

- `s` is a game state type
declarations.title: Game

declarations.comments: Emo8 draw monad which runs some draw operations.
declarations.title: Draw

declarations.comments: Fill the entire canvas with the specified color.
declarations.title: cls

declarations.comments:
Draw the emoji with the specified emoji, size, x and y.

The origin of x and y is the bottom left.
declarations.title: emo

declarations.comments:
Draw the emoji map with the specified emoji map, size, x and y.

The size is one of the emojis'.
declarations.title: emap

declarations.comments: Emo8 sound monad which runs some sound operations.
declarations.title: Sound

declarations.comments:
Play the score with the specified the score, tone and tempo.

The operation is ignored until the score being stopped.
declarations.title: play

declarations.comments: Stop playing with the specified score.
declarations.title: stop

declarations.comments: Emo8 update monad which can access canvas size.
declarations.title: Update

declarations.comments: Get the canvas size given by the `emo8` function.
declarations.title: getCanvasSize

declarations.comments:
Check if the object is outside the canvas.

The origin of x and y is the bottom left.
declarations.title: isOutOfCanvas

declarations.comments: Check if the object collides the frame of the canvas.
declarations.title: isCollideCanvas

declarations.comments:
Emo8 game develepment mode class.

You can save the state to localstrage and visualize it by defining `Encode` and `Decode` instance of the state type.
declarations.title: GameDev

children.comments: It parse `Symbol` type as `EmojiMap` or `Score` value.
children.title: parse

children.comments:
Example
```
mountFuji :: EmojiMap
mountFuji = parse (SProxy :: SProxy Fuji)

type Fuji
  = """
  🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳
  🈳⛅🈳🈳🎌🈳🈳🌧🈳
  🈳🈳🈳🌳🗻🌳🈳🈳🈳
  🈳🈳🌳🗻🗻🗻🌳🈳🈳
  🈳🌳🗻🗻🗻🗻🗻🌳🈳
  🌳🗻🗻🗻🗻🗻🗻🗻🌳
  """
```
children.title: parseEmojiMap

children.comments:
Example
```
beep :: Score
beep = parse (SProxy :: SProxy NHK)

type NHK
  = """
  🎹🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳
  🎹🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳
  🎹🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳
  🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🈳🎹
  """
```
